Sentencas: A numerical model is presented in this work that computes the interdependent fields of flow, temperature, and mass fractions in a single tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: A numerical model coupling the heat and gas species' transport processes in a tubular SOFC

Sentencas: Fuel gas from a pre-reformer is considered to contain H-2, CO, CO2, H2O (vapor), and CH4, so reforming and shift reactions in the cell are incorporated.
Titulo: A numerical model coupling the heat and gas species' transport processes in a tubular SOFC

Sentencas: The model uses mixture gas properties of the fuel and oxidant that are junctions of the numerically obtained local temperature, pressure, and species concentrations, which are both interdependent and related to the chemical and electrochemical reactions.
Titulo: A numerical model coupling the heat and gas species' transport processes in a tubular SOFC

Sentencas: A discretized network circuit of a tubular SOFC was adopted to account for the Ohmic losses and Joule heating from the current passing around the circumference of the cell to the interconnect.
Titulo: A numerical model coupling the heat and gas species' transport processes in a tubular SOFC

Sentencas: In the iterative computation, local electrochemical parameters were simultaneously calculated based on the local parameters of pressure, temperature, and concentration of the species.
Titulo: A numerical model coupling the heat and gas species' transport processes in a tubular SOFC

Sentencas: Upon con vergence of the computation, both local details and the overall performance of the fuel cell are obtained.
Titulo: A numerical model coupling the heat and gas species' transport processes in a tubular SOFC

Sentencas: These numerical results arc important in order to better understand the operation of SOFCs.
Titulo: A numerical model coupling the heat and gas species' transport processes in a tubular SOFC
